         MACRO
         $RXQ  &TARGET,&SEND,&LEN
.*.
.*$MACRO=$RXQ       DATE=04/00/79       SOURCE=UCLA
.*  THIS MACRO WILL MOVE A CHARACTER STRING TO &TARGET.  IF &SEND IS
.*  QUOTED, A LITERAL WILL BE USED, OTHERWISE &SEND IS THE NAME OF THE
.*  SOURCE FIELD.  &LEN IS THE LENGTH OF &TARGET.
.*.
         GBLB  &OMITTED
&OMITTED SETB  0
         AIF   ('&SEND' EQ '' ).NOSEND
         AIF   ('&SEND'(1,1) EQ '(').REGSEND
         AIF   ('&SEND'(1,1) EQ '''').QSEND
         MVC   &TARGET,&SEND
         AGO   .END
.REGSEND MVC   &TARGET,0&SEND
         AGO   .END
.QSEND   MVC   &TARGET,=CL&LEN&SEND
         AGO   .END
.NOSEND  MVC   &TARGET,=CL&LEN' '       NOT SPECIFIED
&OMITTED SETB  1                        OPERAND WAS OMMITTED
.END     ANOP
         MEND
